1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,002
[Marcus] <i>Ma, are you alright?</i>
<i>You got shoved?</i>

2
00:00:03,086 --> 00:00:04,421
[Teresa] <i>I'm all right, son.</i>

3
00:00:04,504 --> 00:00:07,132
<i>Our nurse, Jamilah, lent me a hand anyway.</i>

4
00:00:08,341 --> 00:00:09,634
[Marcus] <i>About Jamilah…</i>

5
00:00:09,718 --> 00:00:11,636
<i>Is she mad at me</i>
<i>because of what happened on the island?</i>

6
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:14,431
<i>I still carry the weight</i>
<i>of their anger and grief.</i>

7
00:00:14,514 --> 00:00:16,808
<i>I can't bring back the lives</i>
<i>that were lost.</i>

8
00:00:17,350 --> 00:00:20,979
You have nothing to worry about, Boss.
I cleaned up all the loose ends.

9
00:00:21,062 --> 00:00:23,106
[Felix] <i>Espina has nothing</i>
<i>to sniff out now.</i>

10
00:00:23,732 --> 00:00:25,525
[Lara] <i>Why do they have to die, Dad?</i>

11
00:00:25,608 --> 00:00:29,946
[Manuel in English] <i>But you've become</i>
<i>so weak. Emotional.</i>

12
00:00:30,488 --> 00:00:33,283
[in English] Stop disappointing me.

13
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:37,037
[Jalil] <i>The more I learn,</i>
<i>the more questions I have.</i>

14
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:40,749
<i>But I know I'm on the right track.</i>
<i>I can save you, Father,</i>

15
00:00:40,832 --> 00:00:44,043
<i>and I'll find out</i>
<i>who masterminded everything.</i>

16
00:00:44,127 --> 00:00:45,587
[tense music playing]

17
00:00:47,172 --> 00:00:48,631
What did you do?!

18
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:52,385
- [man] <i>Come on!</i>
- Let me go!

19
00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:53,803
- [man] <i>Stop resisting!</i>
- [young Lara] <i>Get off me!</i>

20
00:00:53,887 --> 00:00:54,637
[man] <i>What now, huh?</i>

21
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:56,848
- [man] <i>You never listen!</i>
- [young Lara sobs]

22
00:00:58,349 --> 00:01:00,977
[man] You again?
You're really stubborn, aren't you?

23
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:01,978
- [gunshot]
- <i>Where are you going?!</i>

24
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:04,814
My name is Major Manuel Carillo.

25
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:07,609
[Manuel] <i>Don't worry, Lara.</i>
<i>I'll take care of you.</i>

26
00:01:07,692 --> 00:01:13,114
[Manuel] <i>Yes. Datu Rahman Abubakar</i>
<i>killed your parents.</i>

27
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:19,871
[Manuel] <i>I know that you like Lara.</i>

28
00:01:19,954 --> 00:01:22,165
- <i>I'm counting on you to take care of her.</i>
- [Lara shrieks]

29
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:24,876
- <i>I don't want her to get hurt.</i>
- [Lara screams]

30
00:01:24,959 --> 00:01:30,882
<i>As soon as she gets in the way</i>
<i>of our plans…</i>

31
00:01:37,347 --> 00:01:44,187
[mysterious theme music playing]

32
00:01:54,489 --> 00:01:56,741
THE VIRAL VIDEO OF DATU RAHMAN
KILLING TWO POLICE OFFICERS

33
00:01:57,826 --> 00:01:59,285
[pensive music playing]

34
00:01:59,369 --> 00:02:00,954
[Usman] <i>I went to Buster earlier.</i>

35
00:02:01,746 --> 00:02:03,123
I found out

36
00:02:03,206 --> 00:02:05,375
that all the CCTV footage taken
at the time of the crime

37
00:02:05,458 --> 00:02:07,418
was wiped out.

38
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:09,587
[Marcus] <i>You're right.</i>

39
00:02:10,171 --> 00:02:12,006
<i>It wasn't just an accident.</i>

40
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:19,222
[Usman] You killed Condecido and Vinluan
Just to frame Datu Rahman?

41
00:02:22,392 --> 00:02:23,977
What are you really planning?

42
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:30,108
[pensive music playing]

43
00:02:31,609 --> 00:02:35,113
That's what you get
for letting them escape.

44
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:37,740
[scoffs]

45
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:39,617
Unfortunate, right?

46
00:02:39,701 --> 00:02:42,787
The only people who looked up to you died.

47
00:02:44,497 --> 00:02:46,624
They were killed by your own kind.

48
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:47,709
[scoffs]

49
00:02:47,792 --> 00:02:49,419
How unfortunate.

50
00:02:49,502 --> 00:02:50,712
Well…

51
00:02:50,795 --> 00:02:54,465
Those brats picked the wrong guy
to be their role model.

52
00:02:55,508 --> 00:02:57,427
[cackles, choking]

53
00:02:58,469 --> 00:03:01,598
They were young,
and they were good officers.

54
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:04,183
They have more integrity
than you'll ever have.

55
00:03:04,267 --> 00:03:08,771
If you try to insult them again, Montes,
you're going to pay for it.

56
00:03:09,564 --> 00:03:11,149
- [grunts]
- [thuds]

57
00:03:11,232 --> 00:03:13,526
[coughing]

58
00:03:14,068 --> 00:03:15,111
[Montes] You bastard!

59
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:17,906
I'll have them suspend you!

60
00:03:17,989 --> 00:03:21,326
Sabdani, SID is asking for you.
It's about a new assignment.

61
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:24,203
Sir. What assignment?

62
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:28,207
You will be a new member
of the Alpha Task Force.

63
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:29,417
[in English] Congratulations.

64
00:03:30,293 --> 00:03:32,962
What?! Why him?!

65
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:34,088
Montes, why are you on the floor?

66
00:03:34,172 --> 00:03:36,132
Are you filming something?

67
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:38,676
Stand up. You look stupid.

68
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,094
- Go ahead.
- [Montes coughs]

69
00:03:48,937 --> 00:03:51,731
[in English] Madam. Good morning.

70
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:54,275
Coffee?

71
00:03:54,359 --> 00:03:58,488
[somber music playing]

72
00:04:01,491 --> 00:04:03,534
NATIONAL LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY

73
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:09,791
[pensive music playing]

74
00:04:11,751 --> 00:04:12,919
[Marcus] Lara.

75
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:17,340
Director Azuela is speaking
to Espina in his office.

76
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:20,760
Do you think Azuelo will allow Espina
to join our missions?

77
00:04:20,843 --> 00:04:21,678
‪[scoffs]

78
00:04:22,178 --> 00:04:23,263
It's possible.

79
00:04:24,055 --> 00:04:25,390
[in English] Unbelievable.

80
00:04:25,473 --> 00:04:26,933
I did a background check on him.

81
00:04:27,016 --> 00:04:29,477
All of his files were either
redacted or restricted.

82
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:31,521
It makes me wonder, Lara.

83
00:04:32,105 --> 00:04:34,607
What's with this liaison officer
from Mindanao?

84
00:04:34,691 --> 00:04:36,734
Why are all his files redacted?

85
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:38,653
Exactly. That's what I thought too.

86
00:04:38,736 --> 00:04:40,822
It is hard to trust someone we don't know.

87
00:04:41,906 --> 00:04:43,283
Why is he here?

88
00:04:43,366 --> 00:04:47,245
What if he's a part of the conspiracy
you're talking about?

89
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:52,041
[footsteps approaching]

90
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:53,543
They're here.

91
00:04:54,043 --> 00:04:58,923
[tense music playing]

92
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:19,819
- [in English] Ma'am, sir.
- [in English] Ma'am, sir.

93
00:05:23,072 --> 00:05:24,824
[in English] I'm Lara Angeles,
your head agent.

94
00:05:25,742 --> 00:05:27,493
[in English] I'm glad to see
all of you here.

95
00:05:27,577 --> 00:05:30,204
[Jalil] Finally, I'll get to know
all of you.

96
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:32,081
- Sir.
- Sir.

97
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:34,667
Agent Eve Castillo, sir.

98
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:36,711
Agent Andre Flores.

99
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:43,176
Agent Ryan Cruz.

100
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,053
SPO3 Liam Rodriguez.

101
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,515
SPO1 Guzman Sagdani, sir.

102
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:52,101
You're the Muslim?

103
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:54,979
Maranao?

104
00:05:57,190 --> 00:05:58,357
[in English] Yes, sir.

105
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:02,111
I heard great things about you.
Do good, alright?

106
00:06:02,695 --> 00:06:04,030
Thank you very much, sir.

107
00:06:04,113 --> 00:06:06,449
[tense music playing]

108
00:06:12,288 --> 00:06:16,334
[tense music continues]

109
00:06:30,306 --> 00:06:31,974
<i>Moving on to news about the economy,</i>

110
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:35,311
<i>negotiations have continued</i>
<i>for a new investment deal</i>

111
00:06:35,394 --> 00:06:37,730
<i>between the Philippines and Japan.</i>

112
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:40,525
<i>According to Malacañang,</i>
<i>if the deal pushes through,</i>

113
00:06:40,608 --> 00:06:44,403
<i>it will boost the country's economy.</i>

114
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:47,949
<i>It is projected</i>
<i>to provide thousands of jobs</i>

115
00:06:48,032 --> 00:06:51,327
<i>for our countrymen</i>
<i>and open up many businesses.</i>

116
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:54,914
<i>Great news for the people</i>

117
00:06:54,997 --> 00:07:01,254
<i>who are affected by the oil crisis</i>
<i>caused by the war in the Middle East.</i>

118
00:07:01,337 --> 00:07:02,505
[reporter] <i>On the other hand,</i>

119
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:06,425
<i>some Japanese investors</i>
<i>in the team remain skeptical.</i>

120
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:11,097
<i>This is because of the worsening</i>
<i>crime rate in the country.</i>

121
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,473
[Ibrahim groans] There it is.

122
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:15,560
It hasn't even started,
yet we've already lost.

123
00:07:15,643 --> 00:07:18,646
- The country needs help.
- [Malik] I agree.

124
00:07:18,729 --> 00:07:21,858
The company where
my wife works is on the edge.

125
00:07:21,941 --> 00:07:24,235
It's also about to close down
because of its losses.

126
00:07:24,318 --> 00:07:26,028
Life is pretty hard these days.

127
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:29,115
They doubled the price
of diesel and gasoline.

128
00:07:29,198 --> 00:07:30,950
Rates will continue to rise.

129
00:07:31,033 --> 00:07:33,619
I almost get nothing from my deliveries.

130
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:35,329
It only covers the cost of gas.

131
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:39,000
I really hope that deal pushes through.

132
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:42,003
It'll be a huge help to our economy.

133
00:07:42,086 --> 00:07:43,171
[in Arabic] God willing.

134
00:07:43,838 --> 00:07:45,214
- [in Arabic] God willing.
- [in Arabic] God willing.

135
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:47,425
[pensive music playing]

136
00:07:47,508 --> 00:07:50,636
This is the war room of Task Force Alpha.

137
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,555
Whenever we're on the field,

138
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:58,019
Agent Lara Angeles, our head agent,
will be our eyes and ears.

139
00:07:58,644 --> 00:08:03,107
She'll handle our tactical operations
and communications from here.

140
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:04,859
- Remember--
- [in English] Good luck.

141
00:08:06,527 --> 00:08:07,653
Do your best.

142
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:12,158
I'm hoping Agent Reyes
made the right choice with you.

143
00:08:12,241 --> 00:08:17,580
[pensive music continues]

144
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:25,379
The primary mission

145
00:08:25,463 --> 00:08:31,010
is to stop the proliferation
of illegal firearms in the country.

146
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:35,139
And capture the head of the syndicate,

147
00:08:35,223 --> 00:08:37,099
Datu Rahman Abubakar.

148
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:43,272
[tense dramatic music playing]

149
00:08:46,984 --> 00:08:49,028
On the other hand,

150
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:53,783
our government is currently negotiating

151
00:08:54,825 --> 00:08:59,288
a big investment deal
with the Japanese government.

152
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:02,166
This is a great help to our economy.

153
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:05,628
The Japanese have only one condition.

154
00:09:06,128 --> 00:09:11,008
They want us to mitigate
the crime in the country.

155
00:09:11,092 --> 00:09:14,011
We all know the reason behind this.

156
00:09:15,429 --> 00:09:17,807
It's because of illegal weapons.

157
00:09:18,724 --> 00:09:22,853
That's also what makes
these criminals feel confident.

158
00:09:24,105 --> 00:09:25,523
Keep this in mind.

159
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:29,068
This negotiation will proceed depending

160
00:09:29,151 --> 00:09:33,406
on the performance of NLEA of SID

161
00:09:33,489 --> 00:09:37,076
and especially that of Task Force Alpha.

162
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:42,456
You need to eradicate
those criminals as soon as possible!

163
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:47,503
You also need to capture
Datu Rahman Abubakar!

164
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:48,921
[all, in English] Sir, yes, sir!

165
00:09:49,005 --> 00:09:53,843
[suspenseful music playing]

166
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:56,804
- [Buster, in English] Agent Lara! Ma'am!
- [in English] Yes, Buster?

167
00:09:58,431 --> 00:09:59,640
[Buster] Our officers
are currently clashing

168
00:09:59,724 --> 00:10:01,225
with the robbers at Sentro Heritage Bank.

169
00:10:01,309 --> 00:10:02,393
[in English] Heavy fire!

170
00:10:02,476 --> 00:10:04,437
They're asking for
a specialized intervention.

171
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:06,606
- [slams table]
- [in English] Goddammit!

172
00:10:06,689 --> 00:10:08,316
‪[tense dramatic music playing]

173
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:10,776
[in English] Men! Follow me.

174
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:14,196
[tense dramatic music continues]

175
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,865
[Lara, in English] Buster,
make connections.

176
00:10:15,948 --> 00:10:17,074
[in English] Copy, ma'am.

177
00:10:18,326 --> 00:10:22,747
[music intensifies]

178
00:10:31,839 --> 00:10:35,092
[gunshots]

179
00:10:40,973 --> 00:10:43,517
We're currently in front
of the Sentro Heritage Bank

180
00:10:43,601 --> 00:10:47,480
that's currently being robbed
by the notorious group Metal-13!

181
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:48,731
[female reporter] As of now,

182
00:10:48,814 --> 00:10:52,902
police officers are exchanging fire
with the group of robbers.

183
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:54,070
[Axl shouting]

184
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:59,992
- [tense music playing]
- [gunshots]

185
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:07,500
Control, this is Sector 2!

186
00:11:14,465 --> 00:11:17,134
The criminals are armed
with high-powered firearms.

187
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:18,886
We need to take caution.

188
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:22,014
I don't want you to suffer casualties
on your first day.

189
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:23,265
[all, in English] Sir, yes, sir!

190
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:26,268
How could small-time criminals
be armed with RPG weapons?

191
00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:27,353
How did they acquire those?

192
00:11:28,938 --> 00:11:31,690
[Espina] Then that means
illegal syndicates have gotten better.

193
00:11:31,774 --> 00:11:35,903
They no longer just sell mere pistols
to ordinary criminals.

194
00:11:37,905 --> 00:11:39,949
Why are you geared up?
Are you coming with us?

195
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:42,368
Why wouldn't I?

196
00:11:42,451 --> 00:11:44,328
You are not a part of TFA.

197
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:46,789
You might just be a liability to us.

198
00:11:46,872 --> 00:11:48,624
If we were to just talk about wars,

199
00:11:48,707 --> 00:11:51,085
I'd have more experience than all of you.

200
00:11:51,168 --> 00:11:52,378
Probably even more than you.

201
00:11:52,461 --> 00:11:54,338
I don't care about your credentials.

202
00:11:55,172 --> 00:11:56,841
- Life is at stake here.
- [music intensifies]

203
00:11:56,924 --> 00:11:59,677
[Espina] That's why I need to help.
It's part of my assignment here.

204
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:02,388
I can go along
with the operations of any unit,

205
00:12:02,471 --> 00:12:03,389
- especially that of TFA.
- [music subdues]

206
00:12:03,472 --> 00:12:05,599
- This is not your call.
- Sir!

207
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:07,726
My friends are being fired at already.

208
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:10,563
So, will you please
just squabble later instead?

209
00:12:10,646 --> 00:12:12,064
[foreboding music playing]

210
00:12:12,648 --> 00:12:15,317
- [officer, in English] Let's move.
- [Marcus] Okay, move!

211
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:20,739
[tense music playing]

212
00:12:27,204 --> 00:12:31,125
[gunshots]

213
00:12:37,214 --> 00:12:42,303
[tense music continues]

214
00:12:43,554 --> 00:12:46,098
[Axl] Diko! Kid! Get in!

215
00:12:46,182 --> 00:12:47,349
Let's go!

216
00:12:54,773 --> 00:12:56,066
[flesh squelches]

217
00:12:58,569 --> 00:13:00,988
[tense music continues]

218
00:13:01,071 --> 00:13:03,157
- [Jovi] Tommy!
- [man shouts]

219
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:05,784
- [man 1] Let's go!
- [man 2] Carry him! Carry him!

220
00:13:07,495 --> 00:13:09,455
[overlapping dialogue]

221
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:15,419
[suspenseful music playing]

222
00:13:23,928 --> 00:13:28,682
[gunshots]

223
00:13:32,561 --> 00:13:35,481
- [RPG launcher shoots]
- [car explodes]

224
00:13:37,942 --> 00:13:41,612
[Axl shouting] Move! Let's go! Let's move!

225
00:13:42,112 --> 00:13:45,407
[suspenseful music continues]

226
00:13:45,491 --> 00:13:46,992
[tires screeching]

227
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:02,424
[Tommy groans]

228
00:14:03,008 --> 00:14:04,468
- Speed up!
- [driver] Yes, sir.

229
00:14:04,552 --> 00:14:06,053
They might catch up to us!

230
00:14:06,136 --> 00:14:08,722
[Jovi] Um, sir! What are we
going to do about him?

231
00:14:08,806 --> 00:14:14,895
[tense music playing]

232
00:14:17,189 --> 00:14:20,901
[drone camera zooming]

233
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:22,403
[keyboard clacking]

234
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:28,909
[in English] Alpha One, this is Base.
We have visual on target.

235
00:14:28,993 --> 00:14:31,287
- [in English] Black van, heading east.
- [in English] Copy, Base.

236
00:14:31,370 --> 00:14:32,413
[radio static]

237
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:35,666
Felix, turn left at the next corner.

238
00:14:35,749 --> 00:14:38,544
Copy that, sir. Hold on!

239
00:14:38,627 --> 00:14:41,255
[brakes screeching]

240
00:14:41,338 --> 00:14:46,385
[tense music continues]

241
00:14:46,468 --> 00:14:49,597
[Tommy shouts, groans, grunts]

242
00:14:50,639 --> 00:14:53,434
[Jovi] Axl, he's losing a lot of blood!
What are we going to do?!

243
00:14:53,517 --> 00:14:56,061
Jovi, I'm thinking! Just wait!

244
00:14:56,645 --> 00:14:58,564
[Tommy coughing]

245
00:14:58,647 --> 00:15:00,482
- Turn here.
- [Jovi] Let me see.

246
00:15:01,358 --> 00:15:03,652
Boss, we might get caught there.

247
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:05,821
You see my brother's condition, huh?

248
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:08,574
Follow me if you don't want
your skull to explode!

249
00:15:08,657 --> 00:15:10,951
Turn! Turn!

250
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:12,286
[brakes screeching]

251
00:15:12,369 --> 00:15:13,287
[Tommy grunts]

252
00:15:13,787 --> 00:15:15,372
[brakes screeching]

253
00:15:16,749 --> 00:15:18,667
[rapid beeping]

254
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:22,379
Alpha One, they turned right
onto Leopoldo Street.

255
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:23,589
[radio static]

256
00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:27,343
Team, here's the plan.

257
00:15:27,426 --> 00:15:32,014
[tense music playing]

258
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:52,576
[tense music continues]

259
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:53,911
[drone camera zooming]

260
00:15:58,540 --> 00:16:00,125
[brakes screeching]

261
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:08,884
TFA!

262
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:15,391
- [Axl] Give me the money. Hurry, hurry!
- [man 2] Here.

263
00:16:15,474 --> 00:16:19,061
[tense music continues]

264
00:16:24,525 --> 00:16:25,818
[brakes screeching]

265
00:16:26,735 --> 00:16:30,656
- What the… They even scattered money.
- That's smart.

266
00:16:30,739 --> 00:16:31,824
[car horn honking]

267
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:33,158
Move aside!

268
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:34,868
- Move!
- Move!

269
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:38,622
Turn left!

270
00:16:38,706 --> 00:16:40,499
- [brakes screeching]
- [women screaming]

271
00:16:43,460 --> 00:16:45,295
[brakes screeching]

272
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:52,678
Move aside!

273
00:16:52,761 --> 00:16:55,472
- Hey, move it! Hey!
- [Marcus] Move!

274
00:16:56,598 --> 00:17:01,895
[overlapping chatter]

275
00:17:01,979 --> 00:17:07,818
[tense music continues]

276
00:17:14,825 --> 00:17:16,744
- [police sirens blaring]
- [car horn honking]

277
00:17:16,827 --> 00:17:18,746
- They escaped!
- [police sirens blaring]

278
00:17:18,829 --> 00:17:19,747
Where did they go, sir?

279
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:25,210
They turned left onto Florencio Street.

280
00:17:25,294 --> 00:17:27,671
- Hurry!
- Yes, sir.

281
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:29,548
[officer] Move!

282
00:17:30,382 --> 00:17:33,510
- Get on, get on!
- [officer] Let's go, let's go! Quick!

283
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:36,346
[car door shuts]

284
00:17:37,222 --> 00:17:41,268
[brakes screeching]

285
00:17:41,351 --> 00:17:42,436
Where did they go?

286
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:44,646
[Marcus, in English] <i>Base,</i>
<i>we need eyes on target.</i>

287
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:45,564
They're missing.

288
00:17:46,148 --> 00:17:47,858
- [in English] Fly me the drone, Buster.
- [in English] Roger, ma'am.

289
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:52,237
[tense music continues]

290
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:53,947
[drone whirring]

291
00:17:57,534 --> 00:18:01,830
[drone camera beeping]

292
00:18:11,381 --> 00:18:16,804
[drone camera beeping]

293
00:18:18,722 --> 00:18:20,432
[in English] Where are you?

294
00:18:27,147 --> 00:18:28,857
[Jovi] Just a little bit more,
just a little bit more. Come on.

295
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:31,443
I can't… [Tommy exhales]

296
00:18:31,527 --> 00:18:32,861
I can't do it anymore.

297
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:36,156
Hey, don't say that.
You can do it, you hear me?

298
00:18:36,698 --> 00:18:39,910
I told you not to come.
You know this isn't your life.

299
00:18:39,993 --> 00:18:41,995
You know you're reckless, right?

300
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:44,498
[Jovi] Huh. You're too much.

301
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:48,961
Stay with us, Tommy. We're almost there.

302
00:18:49,044 --> 00:18:51,964
Boss, I think we got rid of them.

303
00:18:52,047 --> 00:18:57,803
[drone camera beeping]

304
00:18:59,972 --> 00:19:01,181
[in English] Map! Map.

305
00:19:04,935 --> 00:19:07,688
[in English] Alpha One,
this is Base. Subject spotted.

306
00:19:08,397 --> 00:19:10,274
[drone camera beeping]

307
00:19:13,193 --> 00:19:14,111
Tommy.

308
00:19:14,695 --> 00:19:16,530
Axl! Tommy!

309
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:19,825
Tommy, wake up. Tommy, open your eyes!

310
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:21,034
Axl!

311
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:22,744
- Tommy!
- Tommy!

312
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:25,330
- Tommy, open your eyes!
- Tommy!

313
00:19:25,414 --> 00:19:26,582
Tommy!

314
00:19:26,665 --> 00:19:27,875
Tommy, wake up!

315
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:30,460
[Jovi] Tommy! Tommy, wake up!

316
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:31,461
[Axl] Tommy!

317
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:38,135
[system beeping]

318
00:19:42,389 --> 00:19:44,349
- Turn right!
- [tires screeching]

319
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:49,021
[system beeping]

320
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:55,903
Marcus?

321
00:19:57,988 --> 00:20:00,616
T-They're heading south.
They're heading to--

322
00:20:00,699 --> 00:20:01,533
‪[system beeping]

323
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:04,369
Where?

324
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:06,121
[system beeping]

325
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:09,958
[Marcus] <i>Where, Lara?</i>

326
00:20:14,004 --> 00:20:17,591
Marcus, they're entering
S. Trinidad Hospital now.

327
00:20:17,674 --> 00:20:21,762
[tense music playing]

328
00:20:38,946 --> 00:20:45,786
[tense music continues]

329
00:20:51,541 --> 00:20:52,918
There's still wheezing.

330
00:20:53,418 --> 00:20:56,713
Prepare a nebulizer in case
the patient in bed 3 needs it, okay?

331
00:20:56,797 --> 00:20:58,215
[Jamilah] Copy, Doctor.

332
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:01,635
- [nurse] Hey, Jamilah.
- Hey. Hey!

333
00:21:02,177 --> 00:21:03,262
What happened to your hair?

334
00:21:03,345 --> 00:21:05,889
I'm leaving for Canada, remember?

335
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:08,141
Oh my! Oh right!

336
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:09,393
[whimpers]

337
00:21:09,476 --> 00:21:12,020
- I'm going to miss you.
- I'm going to miss you too.

338
00:21:12,104 --> 00:21:15,023
Hey, don't disappear later
during our break, okay?

339
00:21:15,107 --> 00:21:18,944
Hey, you know,
are you really going through with it?

340
00:21:19,027 --> 00:21:20,570
Don't be sad, sister.

341
00:21:21,154 --> 00:21:23,031
I'll introduce you to someone new
who can be your friend.

342
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:26,285
Gracia! See? See?

343
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:28,245
Oh, whatever.

344
00:21:28,328 --> 00:21:31,373
[gentle music playing]

345
00:21:31,456 --> 00:21:33,667
- [Peter] Is that okay?
- Alright, fine.

346
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:35,585
[Peter] Alright, friend.
See you later, okay?

347
00:21:35,669 --> 00:21:37,421
Yes! See you!

348
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:41,925
[tense music playing]

349
00:21:43,218 --> 00:21:44,553
[tires screeching]

350
00:21:46,054 --> 00:21:47,347
- [rapid gunfire]
- [grunts]

351
00:21:47,431 --> 00:21:48,890
[woman gasps]

352
00:21:49,474 --> 00:21:50,767
[Teresa] What's that?

353
00:21:50,851 --> 00:21:52,144
- [gunshot]
- [grunts]

354
00:21:52,227 --> 00:21:54,146
Let's go! Hurry!

355
00:21:56,398 --> 00:21:57,566
[man 1] This way!

356
00:21:57,649 --> 00:21:59,318
- [man 1] Hurry!
- [man 2] Axl!

357
00:21:59,401 --> 00:22:00,485
[man 1] Doctor!

358
00:22:00,569 --> 00:22:05,782
[tense music continues]

359
00:22:05,866 --> 00:22:06,992
Open the door!

360
00:22:07,951 --> 00:22:09,036
[man shouts]

361
00:22:10,078 --> 00:22:14,708
- Nobody move! Nobody move!
- [people screaming]

362
00:22:14,791 --> 00:22:16,043
[people screaming]

363
00:22:16,126 --> 00:22:18,378
- Nobody move!
- [Jovi] Get down!

364
00:22:19,296 --> 00:22:20,464
[Jovi] Here!

365
00:22:21,631 --> 00:22:22,799
[people whimpering]

366
00:22:22,883 --> 00:22:25,052
[man] Nobody move!

367
00:22:25,135 --> 00:22:26,303
[man] Come here!

368
00:22:26,386 --> 00:22:30,057
[tense music playing]

369
00:22:47,949 --> 00:22:53,371
[tense music continues]

370
00:23:13,683 --> 00:23:16,186
They're dragging innocent people
into this.

371
00:23:16,269 --> 00:23:17,729
[Axl] <i>Do your jobs right</i>
<i>if you don't want us all ending up</i>

372
00:23:17,813 --> 00:23:19,356
<i>in hell together!</i>

373
00:23:19,439 --> 00:23:22,400
[Marcus] <i>All the hostages</i>
<i>are in the emergency room.</i>

374
00:23:22,484 --> 00:23:23,819
- [in English] <i>Secure the perimeter. Move!</i>
- [rapid gunfire]

375
00:23:24,694 --> 00:23:27,823
They need time to save their sibling.
Let's attack them!

376
00:23:27,906 --> 00:23:29,699
We can't rush into this right now.

377
00:23:29,783 --> 00:23:32,577
[Azuelo] We can't afford to mess up
this hostage situation.

378
00:23:32,661 --> 00:23:34,287
[in English] Your negotiator just arrived.

379
00:23:35,664 --> 00:23:37,374
[man grunting]

380
00:23:38,416 --> 00:23:42,003
Just wait, they're calming
things down to gain momentum.

381
00:23:42,879 --> 00:23:47,175
If you want the people here
to get out alive, give us what we need.

382
00:23:47,259 --> 00:23:48,677
[Axl] <i>A large helicopter.</i>

383
00:23:49,344 --> 00:23:50,720
[rapid gunfire]

384
00:23:52,347 --> 00:23:55,934
Doc, BP is 80/60.

385
00:23:56,893 --> 00:23:59,062
What's going on?! What?!

386
00:23:59,146 --> 00:24:00,814
[Lara] <i>I saw Aunt Teresa.</i>

387
00:24:00,897 --> 00:24:02,899
What did you do to him?!

388
00:24:02,983 --> 00:24:05,110
We'll blow your head off.

389
00:24:05,193 --> 00:24:07,863
[suspenseful music ends]
